<exercise checkit-seed="0008" checkit-slug="DL4" checkit-title="Using Laplace Transforms to Solve IVPs">
  <statement>
      <p>
          Explain how to solve the following IVP.
      </p>
      <me>
          -4 \, \delta\left(t - 1\right) = 6 \, {y'} + 2 \, {y''} + 4 \, {y};\qquad
          y(0)=0,
          y'(0)=2
      </me>
      <p>Hint: <m>\frac{1}{x^{2} + 3 \, x + 2} = -\frac{1}{x + 2} + \frac{1}{x + 1}</m>.</p>
  </statement>
  <answer>
      <me>
          \mathcal{L}\{y\}=-\frac{2 \, e^{\left(-s\right)}}{s^{2} + 3 \, s + 2} + \frac{2}{s^{2} + 3 \, s + 2}
      </me>
      <me>
          {y} = -2 \, e^{\left(-t + 1\right)} \mathrm{u}\left(t - 1\right) + 2 \, e^{\left(-2 \, t + 2\right)} \mathrm{u}\left(t - 1\right) + 2 \, e^{\left(-t\right)} - 2 \, e^{\left(-2 \, t\right)}
      </me>
  </answer>
</exercise>
